"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikic/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikic/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikic/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2018-11-29T21:41:57Z", "updated_at": "2019-01-27T17:46:48Z", "closed_at": "2019-01-27T17:46:48Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "In the following test case reduced from SmallVec:\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::mem;\r\n\r\nstruct SV {\r\n    capacity: usize,\r\n    disc: usize,\r\n    data: [usize; 40],\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl SV {\r\n    fn new() -> SV {\r\n        SV { data: unsafe { mem::uninitialized() },\r\n            disc: 0,\r\n            capacity: 0 }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\npub struct L {\r\n    a: SV,\r\n}\r\n\r\npub struct Allocation<T> {\r\n    f: *mut T,\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl<T> Allocation<T> {\r\n    pub fn init(self, value: T) {\r\n        use std::ptr;\r\n        unsafe {\r\n        ptr::write(self.f, value);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n#[inline(never)]\r\npub fn foo(a: Allocation<L>) {\r\n    a.init(L {\r\n        a: SV::new(),\r\n    });\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nproduces\r\n\r\n```asm\r\nexample::foo:\r\n  sub rsp, 344\r\n  xorps xmm0, xmm0\r\n  movaps xmmword ptr [rsp], xmm0\r\n  mov rsi, rsp\r\n  mov edx, 336\r\n  call memcpy@PLT\r\n  add rsp, 344\r\n  ret\r\n```\r\n\r\nmoving `capacity` to the end of the struct gives:\r\n```asm\r\nexample::foo:\r\n  mov qword ptr [rdi], 0\r\n  mov qword ptr [rdi + 328], 0\r\n  ret\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is surprising to me.", "closed_by": {"login": "jrmuizel", "id": 332653, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzMjY1Mw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/332653?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrmuizel", "html_url": "https://github.com/jrmuizel", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrmuizel/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jrmuizel/follo